2022 Beijing area college graduates expected to reach 268,000 - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, Dec. 11 (Xinhua) - The reporter learned from the recent video conference on 2022 Beijing college graduates employment and entrepreneurship jointly held by Beijing Municipal Education Commission and Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau that 2022 Beijing area college graduates are expected to reach 268,000, an increase of The number of graduates in 2022 is expected to reach 268,000, which is 16,000 more than last year. The person in charge of Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau said that the employment work of Beijing college graduates will be deployed in terms of strengthening supply and demand matching, enhancing policy support, widening employment channels, ensuring difficulty assistance, supporting innovation and entrepreneurship, and improving service efficiency. The reporter learned that the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau will build a practice platform, increase the supply of jobs, take the initiative to contact 40 workplace experience bases for college graduates, visit employers and integrate demand and job information; focus on "six batches", i.e., broaden the recruitment of institutions, broaden the recruitment of state-owned enterprises, broaden the recruitment of grassroots projects, broaden the recruitment of state-owned enterprises, and broaden the recruitment of graduates. It focuses on "six batches", i.e. broadening the recruitment of institutions, broadening the recruitment of state-owned enterprises, broadening the recruitment of grass-roots projects, broadening the recruitment into the military, broadening the retention of employment traineeships, broadening the employment driven by entrepreneurship; implementing "one policy for one lifetime" dynamic management, recommending no less than 5 positions for each graduate, ensuring 100% of graduates from difficult families with employment intention to achieve assistance, etc.
